summary: This is an automated email notification from the DOJ's E2 travel system indicating that travel authorization 10982117 for a trip to Stockholm, Sweden has been approved and is pending further approval. The trip is for witness interviews related to the Epstein investigation (case reference 2018R01618).

persons.name: Gnichelexhinca
persons.context: Appears as the recipient of the automated travel authorization email.

events.title: Planned Travel to Stockholm for Witness Interviews
events.description: A DOJ-related trip to Stockholm, Sweden is scheduled to conduct witness interviews for the Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: The document is a DOJ travel authorization email related to the Epstein investigation (case 2018R01618).
A trip to Stockholm, Sweden was approved and scheduled for February 3-8, 2020, for the purpose of witness interviews.
The email indicates ongoing investigative activity by the DOJ into the Epstein case in early 2020.
The travel authorization system used is E2Solutions, part of the DOJ network.
